This article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden at the Omni Shoreham Hotel in Washington, D.C. The President starts by introducing himself as Jill Biden's husband and joking about his Irish heritage. He talks about growing up in a neighborhood where having an Italian last name was important and attending Holy Rosary Catholic school. The President mentions Justice Alito, but it is unclear if he is present. He reminisces about his childhood friend Sonny Daramo and receiving an award from the Sons of Italy, even though he is not Italian. He expresses gratitude for the honor and praises Italian Americans for their contributions to the country and the arts. The President concludes by thanking the audience for allowing him to speak with Jill.